               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18690816-name-220" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18690816-name-220" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18690816-name-220" type="surname" value="POTTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18690816-name-220" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>DAVID POTTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a porter at the St. John's Wood Station of the Metropolitan Railway—on the evening of the 4th August I was on the engine of a train which left Baker Street at 5.38—on getting through the tunnel, I saw the prisoner with his hand raised—I watched him, and as the engine passed him he threw a brick at the train; it entered the window of a third-class carriage—I got off the train at St. John's Wood Station, and went and took the prisoner; he was in an in closure by the side of the line, up a pear tree—when he saw me he said, "I did not throw the stone"—I had not said anything about a stone, I had scarcely got to the tree—I am quite certain he is the boy—I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I did not throw the stone; there were more besides me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18690816-name-221" type="witnessName">
